C-PTSD 
- covers all ages. For example, it could be acquired by anyone who is under the care of another, e.g. nursing home, profound ASD.
- requires trauma to be repeated and uncontrollable
- may or may not have a stable caregiver relationship, but unstable caregiving is not relevant

Childhood C-PTSD 
- C-PTSD but only from ages (0-18)
- uncontrolled trauma, but with a stable caregiving figure. E.g.: living in a warzone, natural disasters.

DTD
- must be acquired during the developmental period (ages 0-18)
- primarily an unstable caregiving relationship (caregiver is both the source of abuse and survival)


